<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
This is cross-posted over at the Forum, under the Modules discussion. Sorry about that, but I realized a better place for this is here after posting there. <p>
The three I can think of are (please post more if you're inspired): 
</p>
<p>
1) Pirate. As in Umbar. A rogue-like character. 
</p>
<p>
2) Shipwright. Like Cirdan et. al. Perhaps akin to a loremaster. 
</p>
<p>
3) Mariner.  I forget his name just now. You know who. Weaker melee type? with some other skills to compensate? 
</p>
<p>
Specific abilities for Nautical Classes would include speed bonuses in water, and resistance to drowning. Better luck? Sailors must have some luck to survive, I believe. 
</p>
<p>
Can't think of anything else at the moment. 
</p>
<p>
-Solorin 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Historically, almost all sailors couldn't swim, so I think resistance to drowning doesn't work, nor does a speed bonus in water (unless we somehow manage to code a boat!) However, if you want to give a nautical class a major bonus, give it a resistance to water attack. (Sailors withstand the worst sorts of spray/swells/etc.)  
</p>
<p>
Then, for good measure, add:  
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 vulnerability to fire 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 innate rcold after a certain CL (basic rcold, not doubled) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 reduced chance to slip on ice 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 levitation (for a "climbing bonus") once a certain CL is reached (that'll give you an effective rdrowning anyway) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 DEX bonus  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 INT penalty 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 small luck bonus 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 "Spyglass": telepathy (only over water) once a certain CL is reached 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 "Weathereye": after a certain CL, intrinsic ability to detect monsters with air or water attacks, or any environmental air/water effects like fog/etc 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 access to trapping (via knots... okay, maybe that's hokey <img src="./wiki/starshine/img/smile4.png" alt=";)" height="15" width="15"> ) 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
All of that's my $0.02, of course. <img src="./wiki/starshine/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
<strong>Solorin</strong>: Wow. Good stuff. Thanks for fleshing out my vagarious notion. Earendil, Earendil the Mariner, that was it. Now, that I consider it though Mariners would probrably be more like rangers. Not really much chance for melee onboard a ship, unless your a pirate of course.  
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Thanks. I'm a closet C.S. Forester fan. A great read, btw, if you can make it through the old-style English. Oh, and also btw -- it really doesn't relate to the game, but if you think melee doesn't happen shipboard, you should read that series or some history books <img src="./wiki/starshine/img/smile4.png" alt=";)" height="15" width="15"> Oh yes, and sailors in olden ages should probably run through food faster than most, to reflect their nutritional deficiencies...  
</p>
